dataset.title: MCR LTER: Coral Reef: Ocean Currents and Biogeochemistry: salinity, temperature and current at CTD and ADCP mooring FOR04 from 2004 ongoing

abstract.para: Moored and bottom mounted instrumentation (ADCP, CTD, thermistors, wave-tide meters) sampled year-round on the reef of Moorea Island, French Polynesia at site FOR04. Sampling began in 2005. All data have been interpolated onto a 20 min grid. ADCP data are orgainized into 1-meter bins, measured as height from the bottom, to a maximum of 20 bins. All bins may not be filled, and although post processing attempted to exclude data from bins 'above the surface', users need to exercise caution with the near surface bins. CTD parameters include Pressure, Temperature, Conductivity, Salinity and Density. The two moored CTD packages are located approximately 5 and 14 meters above the bottom, and there are up to 5 additional temperature thermistors spaced vertically along the mooring line and 2 bottom mounted thermistors in the vicinity of the mooring at 10 and 20 meter depth. A bottom mounted wave-tide meter provides a measure of significant wave height and dominant wave period at a 2 hour sampling interval.

geographicCoverage.geographicDescription: Moorea, French Polynesia, FOR04 on SE shore

description.para: This is an ongoing dataset. Data are added twice per year. There is a delay between collection of raw data and the analysis. Public release is not delayed after data is processed.

changeHistory.comment: Extensive metadata revisions to improve column descriptions in the largest data table. For example, titles and labels are re-named to more easily identify temperature data.
Revision 29 only changes one attributeName, replacing spaces with underscores.
Revision 30 is a whole year new data appended (normally two updates per year).

section.title: Data Handling:
section.para: Data are filtered and processed to derive calculated data products and for quality control. Raw data are recorded at a short time interval, then processed to remove noise and resampled at 3 points per hour.

protocol.title: Mooring Time Series Protocol - Matlab Data Processing

section.title: Quality Assurance for aggregate completeness
section.para: Data coverage fraction is between 0 and 1 and is defined as the number of measurements actually available divided by the number of measurements theoretically possible in the time aggregation bin.
